dpul.title: Treasures of the East Asian Library Reindex issues

comments.body:
Today I discovered that one of our DPUL machines was not able to connect to redis. That explains this error perfectly: Any time the workers on that box picked up the updates from Figgy, they tried to enque the index update but it got dropped because it couldn't enqueue the job. So sometimes it would have worked (when the worker that could connect picked up up) and sometimes it didn't (when the worker with connection issues picked it up). The redis connection is now fixed and that should resolve this issue. 

Details of the fix are in https://github.com/pulibrary/dpul/issues/1491#issuecomment-1875942190

princeton_ansible.title: Can not SSH on to EC2 connection

comments.body:
@acozine @hectorcorrea had the error and this is what showed in the ssh
```
$ ssh -vvvv pulsys@44.197.15.236
OpenSSH_9.4p1, LibreSSL 3.3.6
debug1: Reading configuration data /Users/correah/.ssh/config
debug1: /Users/correah/.ssh/config line 1: Applying options for *
debug1: Reading configuration data /etc/ssh/ssh_config
debug1: /etc/ssh/ssh_config line 21: include /etc/ssh/ssh_config.d/* matched no files
debug1: /etc/ssh/ssh_config line 54: Applying options for *
debug2: resolve_canonicalize: hostname 44.197.15.236 is address
debug3: expanded UserKnownHostsFile '~/.ssh/known_hosts' -> '/Users/correah/.ssh/known_hosts'
debug3: expanded UserKnownHostsFile '~/.ssh/known_hosts2' -> '/Users/correah/.ssh/known_hosts2'
debug1: Authenticator provider $SSH_SK_PROVIDER did not resolve; disabling
debug3: ssh_connect_direct: entering
debug1: Connecting to 44.197.15.236 [44.197.15.236] port 22.
debug3: set_sock_tos: set socket 3 IP_TOS 0x48
```

In this particular case the issue was that my IP address while on the VPN was not covered in the ranges that the security group in AWS for this machine allows. I added my IP address as indicated in these instructions https://github.com/pulibrary/pul-it-handbook/blob/main/services/aws.md#trouble-shooting (thanks @carolyncole) and I am able to SSH again.

Apologies, I did not mean to remove the firestone renovations line from the existing prod file.  Also, I'm not sure why the first two commits for "hishi" are included in this PR.  This is for another set of changes on a different branch that was resolved months ago.  Let me know if I should just delete this and try again...
Closing this PR without merging.  It is better to resolve the issues offline
